Proposal for improving the global online discourse through personalised comment ordering on all websitesPublished on December 6, 2023 6:51 PM GMT<br/><br/><p> This is a description of a project I&#39;ve been thinking about making in the last few weeks. I&#39;m looking for feedback and collaborators. [BetterDiscourse] name is provisional.</p><h2>问题</h2><p>Social media promote tribalism and polarisation. Communities drift towards groupthink <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/j2W3zs7KTZXt2Wzah/how-do-you-feel-about-lesswrong-these-days-open-feedback?commentId=X7iBYqQzvEgsppcTb">even if they were specifically founded to be strongholds for rational discourse and good epistemics</a> .</p><p> Comments sections to media articles and YouTube videos are frequently dominated by support of the author (or the pundit guest of the show), finding rational critique there is time consuming, like finding a needle in a haystack.</p><p> X&#39;s <a href="https://vitalik.ca/general/2023/08/16/communitynotes.html">Community Notes</a> , <a href="http://pol.is">pol.is</a> , and its development variant <a href="https://viewpoints.xyz/">viewpoints.xyz</a> are universally louded, but they all use the principle of “finding the most uncontroversial common ground” which is by definition low-information for the discourse participants (because most of them should already be expected to be on board with this common ground).</p><p> Big Audacious Goal aka mission statement: <strong>improve the global online discourse</strong> . Among humans, anyway, but perhaps <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/tag/debate-ai-safety-technique-1">AI debate</a> could benefit from the mechanics that I describe below as well.</p><h2>解决方案</h2><p>Each user has a state-space model ( <a href="https://twitter.com/_albertgu">SSMs are on fire right now</a> ) that represents their levels of knowledge in this or that fields, beliefs, current interests, ethics, and aesthetics, in order to <strong>predict whether the user will find a particular comment insightful/interesting/surprising, clarifying, mind-changing, or reconciling.</strong></p><p> To provide feedback to the model, a browser extension adds the corresponding reactions (along with negative counterparts to the above reactions: “Nothing new”, “Unclear/Muddled”, “Disagree”, “Combative/Inflaming”) to the comment on the popular platforms: Reddit, YouTube, X/Twitter. (During a later stage, [BetterDiscourse] may also host comments for media which don&#39;t have comments themselves, such as NYT or YouTube videos with comments disabled, and display them through the same browser extension, like <a href="https://glasp.co/">glasp.co</a> is doing.)</p><p> Then, when the user opens a media or a comment section on some site, the browser extension simply sorts the comments for them <span class="footnote-reference" role="doc-noteref" id="fnrefo2509psvxb9"><sup><a href="#fno2509psvxb9">[1]</a></sup></span> .</p><p> I think this should very valuable already in this completely local regime, however, things may get even more interesting, and to recapitulate the “collaborative filtration power” of Community Notes, <a href="http://Pol.is">Pol.is</a> , and Viewpoints.xyz, <strong>(active) users&#39; feedbacks are aggregated to bubble up the best comments up for new users, or for users who choose not to vote actively to tune their predictive model well</strong> . Furthermore, when users with a similar state-space already voted positively for comments that their models didn&#39;t predict then such comments could be shown earlier to other users in the same state-space cluster, overriding the predictions of their models.</p><p> More concretely, [BetterDiscourse] creates two models:</p><ul><li> The <strong>predictive model</strong> inputs user&#39;s state, language embedding of the comment (or the original piece of content itself, such as an article), native rating/vote signals for the comment on the host platform, and existing reactions to the comment on [BetterDiscourse] ; outputs expected user&#39;s reactions to the content or comment.</li><li> The <strong>transition model</strong> inputs user&#39;s state, language embedding of the content, and user&#39;s actual reactions to the content (or lack thereof), and outputs the next user&#39;s state.</li></ul><h2> Data and delivery</h2><p> The user&#39;s state and model inference should, <a href="https://medium.com/swlh/data-slavery-and-decentralized-emancipation-ec9cc1265608">of course</a> , stay local to the user, and the models themselves open sourced.</p><p> The initial data for training the models should either be crowdsourced (harder and longer), or collected with the assistance of LessWrong (easier). As you may have noticed, LessWrong already has all the needed reactions. Actually, I&#39;d say that LessWrong <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/ByqKwsYK6rH6AYNDY/reacts-now-enabled-on-100-of-posts-though-still-just#Iterating_on_the_react_palette">has too many of them</a> , I think collapsing them to just 8 mentioned above, plus general upvote and downvote would be enough.</p><p> LessWrong is also uniquely well suited for the bootstrapping data for training the models because I think due to the inclinations of the audience, just putting all these reactions on the constant display in the UI (along up/down and agree/disagree that are already there, it&#39;s just three more pairs) should be sufficient to incentivise the users to react to the comments with the needed density.</p><p> Another aspect that makes LessWrong an ideal beach-head community for testing the mechanics of [BetterDiscourse] is that LessWrong is a relatively small community, so testing the advantages of [BetterDiscourse] for new users or users who don&#39;t actively vote (or simply un-logged in readers) doesn&#39;t require too big critical mass of initial active voters.</p><p> Still, LessWrong (or crowdsourced) data would be sufficient to train only a relatively small and not very capable predictive model. To make the predictive model more powerful, the SSM should be continuously re-trained on the data from at least a large portion of production users. I didn&#39;t think hard about this yet, and I&#39;m not an expert in federated learning and differential privacy, but I bet there should be some way to organise the model training in a privacy-preserving (and benefit-distributing, see below ） 方式。</p><h2>经济学</h2><p>Reading comments and diligent voting is time-consuming work. It should be compensated by a token, similar to Brave&#39;s <a href="https://basicattentiontoken.org/">Basic Attention Token</a> .</p><p> Reactions to comments to a particular content piece are aggregated and distributed by special types of nodes (let&#39;s call them Story Nodes), which could perhaps itself be open sourced, and spun up for arbitrary communities, including those where the content and comments are not public 。</p><p> Story Nodes charge the token for accessing the best consensus sorting of comments. It is bought by people who don&#39;t want to spend a lot of time reading through the comments and voting, but want to access comments with the best ordering, saving their time and maximising value from reading. Story Nodes share the tokens with the users who reacted to the comments “well”.</p><p> Credit assignment to the users is not trivial here: to prevent abuse of the system with junk voting, it should be based on free energy reduction (FER), ie, formally, just the difference in the <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/tag/free-energy-principle">free energy</a> of the Story Node before and after receiving a reaction from the user <span class="footnote-reference" role="doc-noteref" id="fnrefppruaxulap"><sup><a href="#fnppruaxulap">[2]</a></sup></span> .</p><p> Users who intend to make [BetterDiscourse] their income source (perhaps, there <i>should</i> be such users to reach a sufficient voting density on many resources) will try to react to comments that don&#39;t have many reactions yet (to maximise Story Node&#39;s FER from their reaction) and that are expected to still receive a lot of readership in the future: Story Nodes will pay out to the voters based on their expected token revenue projects from the moment of receiving reactions.</p><p> Story Nodes are spun up by Story Node operators when they predict the story is going to be popular (eg, a new video on a popular YouTube channel). When the attention to the story has died out, the Story Node is shut down, thus there are no amortised storage costs.</p><p> The real question is whether the cost of all inference happening on all nodes involved in [BetterDiscourse] has dropped below the market value that [BetterDiscourse] delivers which is optimising time and value from reading comments.我不确定这一点。 But even if this is <i>currently</i> (end of 2023) not the case, we should expect this to become so in one or two years, as the cost of inference continues to drop exponentially.</p><h3> Secondary data uses and cross-sector integrations</h3><p> The predictive model could directly be used for prioritising content the user doesn&#39;t have time to process in full, such as newsletters, posts on Telegram, Mastodon and RSS feeds. This is not the initial use-case because this would probably require very big and powerful SSM to work well. Such a big SSM couldn&#39;t be trained initially. Also, the impact is limited because the closed platforms such as Facebook, X/Twitter, YouTube, and Reddit won&#39;t permit accessing their feeds programmatically.</p><p> Building the whole content recommendation and delivery platform (such as Substack) should be treated as a separate problem. If [BetterDiscourse] gains a lot of users, these platforms will themselves be interested to buy reactions from some [BetterDiscourse] to train their recommendation models such that if the platform later onboards a person who is already a [BetterDiscourse] user, they will receive good recommendations from the very beginning, and then continuously respond to their changing state.</p><p> Apart from Story Nodes and content platforms, users could also sell their reactions to market researchers and political researchers, or donate it to social scientists and alignment researchers.</p><p> There are also many opportunities for leveraging user&#39;s state as inputs for other personal AI apps, such as networking (dialogue-matching) app, movie or event recommendation app, psychotherapy app, or a general personal assistant.</p><h2> Spam and manipulation</h2><p> There are a few strategies to combat spam and opinion manipulation on [BetterDiscourse].</p><p> First, to rule out bots, some Story Nodes may permit receiving reactions only from users with some kind of <a href="https://vitalik.eth.limo/general/2023/07/24/biometric.html">proof of humanness</a> identity, such as <a href="https://worldcoin.org/">Worldcoin</a> .</p><p> However, this is not necessary in principle, and I&#39;m curious what will happen with the discourse if AI agents can participate as voters, apart from depriving real human users of all opportunity to earn by using the system. We can speculate how this could lead to the emergence of “AI opinion leaders”, or be connected with <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/tag/debate-ai-safety-technique-1">debate</a> , but this is outside of the scope of this post.</p><p> If voting is human-only, people could try to game [BetterDiscourse] for earning more tokens. If that happens to be the case, some standard anti-fraud data analysis can be used, and financed by Story Node operators.</p><h2>其他风险</h2><p>The main risk that I see in the whole project is the product risk: that is, people won&#39;t want to prioritise informationally best comments, and that their main motivation for reading comments is confirming their pre-existing worldviews. This is sort of what is customary to expect, but leaning into my optimism bias, I should plan as if this is not the case. (Otherwise, aren&#39;t we all doomed, anyway?)</p><p> If it proves that letting AI to react to comments leads to bad results or rampant spam and manipulation (battling which requires so much compute that it makes the whole system uneconomical), gatekeeping reactions aggregation on proof-of-humanness will limit the initial reach of the system a lot, ie, only to the people who are already have a proof-of-humanness ID, which is well less than 1% of people today.</p><hr><p> <i>If you are interested in building [BetterDiscourse], please leave a comment, or send me an e-mail at leventov.ru@gmail.com.</i></p><hr><p> Thanks to Rafael Kaufmann and Connor McCormick (folks from <a href="https://digitalgaia.earth/">Digital Gaia</a> and my fellows in <a href="https://gaiaconsortium.org/">Gaia Consortium</a> ) for many discussions that have led to the development of this project idea. </p><ol class="footnotes" role="doc-endnotes"><li class="footnote-item" role="doc-endnote" id="fno2509psvxb9"> <span class="footnote-back-link"><sup><strong><a href="#fnrefo2509psvxb9">^</a></strong></sup></span><div class="footnote-content"><p> YouTube makes this harder by not loading many comments at once.</p></div></li><li class="footnote-item" role="doc-endnote" id="fnppruaxulap"> <span class="footnote-back-link"><sup><strong><a href="#fnrefppruaxulap">^</a></strong></sup></span><div class="footnote-content"><p> Even this is not the end of the credit assignment story. For example, the credit that initially went to a good-sounding but misleading comment should be forwarded to “rebuttal” replies. I don&#39;t have a complete vision of credit assignment in [BetterDiscourse] yet.</p></div></li></ol><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/aRwBw8W7G9gvLFJSW/proposal-for-improving-the-global-online-discourse-through#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/aRwBw8W7G9gvLFJSW/proposal-for-improving-the-global-online-discourse-through aRwBw8W7G9gvLFJSWRoman Leventov Wed, 06 Dec 2023 18:51:38 GMT 
Google Gemini AnnouncedPublished on December 6, 2023 4:14 PM GMT<br/><br/><p>谷歌刚刚发布了 Gemini，哈萨比斯声称“在我们测试的 50 个不同主题领域中，它的性能与这些领域中最优秀的人类专家一样好”</p><blockquote><p>最先进的性能</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>我们一直在严格测试 Gemini 模型并评估其在各种任务中的性能。从自然图像、音频和视频理解到数学推理，Gemini Ultra 的性能在大型语言模型 (LLM) 研发中使用的 32 个广泛使用的学术基准中的 30 个上超过了当前最先进的结果。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p> Gemini Ultra 的得分高达 90.0%，是第一个在 MMLU（大规模多任务语言理解）上超越人类专家的模型，该模型结合了数学、物理、历史、法律、医学和伦理学等 57 个科目来测试知识和解决问题的能力。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>我们新的 MMLU 基准方法使 Gemini 能够利用其推理能力在回答难题之前更仔细地思考，从而比仅使用第一印象有显着改进。</p></blockquote><p>它似乎还可以理解视频，这对于多模式模型来说是新的（GPT-4 目前无法做到这一点）。</p><br/><br/><a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/9Xh2PyMzNDu3yEHqR/google-gemini-announced#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/9Xh2PyMzNDu3yEHqR/google-gemini-announced 9Xh2PyMzNDu3yEHqRg-w1 Wed, 06 Dec 2023 16:14:07 GMT 
Based Beff Jezos and the AccelerationistsPublished on December 6, 2023 4:00 PM GMT<br/><br/><p>福布斯似乎决定对 e/acc 创始人 Based Beff Jezos 的身份进行人肉搜索。他们使用语音匹配软件来做到这一点。</p><p>考虑到这件事发生了，杰佐斯拥有了它，而不是希望这一切都消失，而且人们都在谈论他，这似乎是一个很好的时机来报道这个“贝夫·杰佐斯”角色，并为他继续出现创造一个参考点稍后再起来。</p><p>如果这与您的兴趣无关，您可以而且应该跳过这一点。</p><span id="more-23619"></span><h4 class="wp-block-heading">不要Doxx人</h4><p>第一件事：坏福布斯。 <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/ESYudkowsky/status/1731019297781436915">停下来。不要 doxx 人。</a>不要用狐狸来 doxx 人。不要用带有奶油奶酪和熏鲑鱼的百吉饼来欺骗人们。不要对发帖的人进行人肉搜索。不要对那些吹牛的人进行人肉搜索。即使那个人提倡的政策可能会杀死你，杀死你所爱的每个人，并以他们的热力学上帝的名义消灭宇宙中所有源自地球的价值，也不要对他进行人肉搜索。</p><p>如果你对他们进行了人肉搜索，至少要承认<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/xlr8harder/status/1730785977755402557">你对他们进行了人肉搜索</a><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/HipCityReg/status/1730793119170343044">，而不是否认</a>。</p><p>如果您认为有必要发送消息，那么使用具有累积声誉的笔名绝对没有任何问题。不管你对杰佐斯有什么看法，他相信某件事，并且拥有它。</p><h4 class="wp-block-heading">贝夫·杰佐斯提倡采取他认为可能会杀死所有人的行动</h4><p>Jezos 匿名说了些什么？杰佐斯是否积极支持他认为可能导致全人类死亡的事情，并且他直言不讳地说他对此没有意见？</p><p>是的。在这种情况下确实如此。 <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/eshear/status/1730830347892593031">但他再次相信，这实际上是件好事。</a></p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p> Emmet Shear：我和贝夫喝过一次酒，他看起来是一个聪明、好人……他想从量子泡沫中培养出一位年长的机器神，但我可以看出这只是因为他认为这对每个人来说都是最好的。</p><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/teortaxesTex/status/1731246730480431255">TeortaxesTex（不同的线索</a>）：>;在 e/acc 宣言中，当说“人类的首要目标是保护意识之光”时……>;意识实体的福祉在其世界观的道德中*没有分量* </p><figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3xoThNNYgZmTCpEAB/tfffu6fbygz0axiszf6r" alt="Image" title="图像"></figure><p><a target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4bf79d49-d455-4ce5-a390-b38ebffb1ca6_1170x899.jpeg" rel="noreferrer noopener"></a></p></blockquote><p>我相当有信心 Jezos 会认为这些陈述是准确的，并且这就是“This Is What Beff Jezos 实际上相信” <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BU2EUfinwHo&amp;ab_channel=GeorgeW.Bush">可以适当地显示在屏幕上的</a>地方。</p><p>我想澄清的是： <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/daniel_271828/status/1728379010252673193">调查显示</a>，只有一小部分人（大约 15%）愿意在 Twitter 报告中贴上“e/acc”标签来支持这一立场。 #NotAllEacc。但真正的创始人 Beff Jezos？我相信是的，是的。</p><h4 class="wp-block-heading">一些争论的问题</h4><p>因此，如果贝夫·杰佐斯 (Beff Jezos) 这么认为，他就应该这么说。我会带着这个麦克风来到这里。</p><p>我希望<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/BasedBeffJezos/status/1732104085351039225">他能参加德瓦克什·帕特尔（Dwarkesh Patel）提出的辩论</a>，尽管这种联系表明杰佐斯不愿意以文明的方式对待那些他不同意的人，除非完全蔑视。 <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/BasedBeffJezos/status/1732168973830238495">然后 Jezos 对以任何形式辩论 Dwarkesh 的提议提出了质疑，同时直截了当地指责 Dwarkesh ……加密货币欺诈</a>并想要炒作垃圾币？</p><p>我的意思是，即使按照 2023 年 12 月的标准，哇。这家伙。</p><p>我想知道杰佐斯是否相信他对那些他不同意的人所说的荒谬？</p><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/dwarkesh_sp/status/1732177146158989502">作为回应，德瓦克什提出在没有主持人的情况下进行直播并进行直播，以解决任何不公平问题</a>。正如预期的那样，尽管 Jezos 之前非常希望出现在 Dwarkesh 的播客上，但这一提议还是被拒绝了。这是一种模式，正如 Jezos <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/DanHendrycks/status/1651740865159901184">之前在与 Dan Hendrycks 的辩论中退出一样</a>。</p><p>杰佐斯现在声称他将与康纳·莱希进行辩论，我也认为康纳·莱希是一个足够有价值的对手。 <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/BasedBeffJezos/status/1732175108201198002">他们说是</a>， <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://manifold.markets/ZviMowshowitz/will-based-beff-jezos-debate-a-wort">预测市场说83%</a> 。</p><p>他们尚未宣布主持人。我在 Twitter 上推荐了 Roon，如果他心情不好的话，另一个不错的选择可能是 Vitalik Buterin。</p><p> Eliezer Yudkowsky 指出（ <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/ESYudkowsky/status/1732249519776301161">全文转载如下</a>），理论上他可以与 Beff Jezos 进行辩论，但实际上他们似乎并没有就哪些行为导致哪些结果存在分歧，因此不清楚他们到底会辩论什么？在尤德科斯基（我同意他对此的理解）看来，分歧似乎指向结果并说“……那太糟糕了”，而杰佐斯则说“很好”。</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p> Eliezer Yudkowsky：我愿意与以前有长期人身攻击记录的人辩论的条件是，辩论完全是关于事实问题，例如“如果你构建一个人工智能并运行它，实际上会发生什么？”，并且有一位主持人了解这一条件并将强制执行。</p><p>我不知道与 @BasedBeffJezos 进行这样的辩论会是什么样子。事实上，据我了解，我们的立场是：</p><p>埃利以泽：如果有人建立了人工智能，它就会杀死所有人。不管哪个公司、哪个国家，地球上的每个人都死了，包括他们。</p><p>我的 Beff Jezos 立场模型：是的。</p><p>埃利以泽：我不能说“这很糟糕”，因为这是一种价值判断，而不是经验预测。但这里有一些进一步的背景，说明为什么我认为我预测的事件进程落入了我认为糟糕的结果中：我预测 ASI 会消灭我们，并吞噬周围的星系，不会希望周围有其他快乐的人，或者甚至自己变得幸福。我无法预测ASI实际上会用什么来平铺可到达的宇宙，但即使从一个非常国际化和包容性的立场来看，试图避免碳沙文主义，我预测它将与“用微小的平铺一切”处于相同的道德划分中。菱形”[1]。</p><p>建造巨大的、永恒的、复杂的时钟比“微小的菱形”更复杂。但如果没有人看过这些复杂的时钟，并觉得它们的持久性令人印象深刻，并对时钟的复杂功能感到高兴，我认为这与时钟只是微小的菱形相同的道德结果。我的预测范围极其广泛，其细节我无法猜测；几乎所有的度量都属于“坏”等价划分；即使考虑到 ASI 人类创造者所谓的聪明计划正在被投射到那个空间。</p><p>我对 Beff Jezos 立场的模型：我不太关心你的这个预测，所以我不同意它。只要熵增加的速度比其他情况下快，我就很高兴。</p><p>我已经暂时解锁了@BasedBeffJezos，以防他对此做出我认为的实质性回应，例如，“我实际上预测，作为关于宇宙的经验事实，根据几乎任何一套设计原则构建的人工智能都会关心认为其他有情心本身就是目的，并惊奇地看待宇宙，因为他们花时间和精力去有意识地体验；人类的后代将提升到与他们自己平等，所有那些且只有那些要求提升的人类；禁止在他们管辖的所有地区进行智慧奴役或更大的恐怖；我认为这一立场是关于物理现实的公众所知的真理，而不仅仅是出于信仰而重复的话语；所有这一切都是我立场的关键，如果我确信事实并非如此，我就会退缩，不会毁灭所有人类生命。”</p><p>我认为这就是一些电子/ACC 所相信的——尽管数量比我们想象或希望的要少。我认为贝夫·杰佐斯并不这么认为。</p><p>虽然我希望杰佐斯有话要说，但我不认为这种说法会与实证预测有所不同，即他所偏爱的政策是否会杀死地球上的所有人，并用不关心爱的思想取代我们。根据我对他的理解，这不是他的目的。</p></blockquote><p>无论辩论、礼貌和相关问题如何，我和埃利泽·尤德科夫斯基一样，强烈反对杰佐斯的未来计划。我认为以这种方式排列宇宙原子是一个非常令人震惊的愚蠢想法，它不会提供任何我看重的东西，因此我们也许不应该这样做？</p><p>相反，我认为“对每个人来说都是最好的”，我个人的偏好涉及到人们的生存。公平地说，大多数采用“e/acc”标签的人也是如此。再说一遍#NotAllEacc。我的大多数模型并不涉及他们正确思考这些场景。</p><p>但让我们进行一下辩论吧。</p><h4 class="wp-block-heading">对 Doxx 的回应</h4><p>我还没有看到任何人为《福布斯》对 Beff Jezos 进行人肉搜索的决定进行辩护。我看到讨论这一事件的每个人都以最强烈的措辞谴责了这一事件。</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p> Eliezer Yudkowsky：我们几乎在所有事情上都存在分歧，但对《福布斯》对相关 e/acc 进行人肉搜索的做法感到非常不满。许多社会问题是我们不能说的。建立具有声誉的假名是一种补救措施。当人们变得更加害怕说话时，社会就会变得更糟。</p></blockquote><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.astralcodexten.com/p/open-thread-305">斯科特·亚历山大（Scott Alexander）走得最远，原因显而易见。</a></p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p>假名加速主义领袖“Beff Jezos” <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/BasedBeffJezos/status/1730788753567048104">被<em>福布斯人</em>肉搜索</a>。我在这些问题上不同意 Jezos 的观点，但想重申，人肉搜索是不可接受的。我没有很好的反击方式，但出于同情，我已经屏蔽了 X 上的负责记者（Emily Baker-White），将避免在该博客上链接<em>福布斯</em>至少一年，并且永远不会接受采访致任何<em>《福布斯》</em>记者——如果您认为我可以做其他事情，请告诉我。辩护者说我的人肉搜索是可以的，因为我在其他地方透露了我的真实姓名，所以我是“自找的”；他们通过在 Jezos 的播客节目中应用语音识别软件来抓到他，所以我希望这些人也同意 Jezos 的案件越界了。</p><p>另外，我对加速论者未能提出真正的论点或回应批评有很多抱怨，但现在是记住他们仍然比媒体及其盟友做得更好的好时机。</p></blockquote><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/BasedBeffJezos/status/1730788753567048104">杰佐斯本人对这篇文章的回应是拥有这篇文章</a>，承认自己的身份，宣布胜利，并开始炒作他不再处于秘密模式的初创公司。</p><p>这是完全正确的战略玩法。</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/BasedBeffJezos/status/1730799840291147819">Beff Jezos</a> ：doxx 始终是一个陷阱。他们陷入其中。时间成倍指数加速。</p><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1730795974631534778">Roon</a> ：这是一个 doxx 还是一个泡芙片？</p><p> Beff Jezos：他们要发送我的所有详细信息，所以我接了电话。贝夫·里兹很强大。</p></blockquote><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.piratewires.com/p/thot-police-forbes-has-doxed-beff">可以预见的是，迈克·索拉纳（Mike Solana）是对这种卑鄙的人肉搜索最愤怒的</a>人，而且他对《福布斯》文章认为贝夫·杰佐斯（Beff Jezos）的议程实际上很糟糕感到很生气。</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p>迈克·索拉纳：贝夫的愿望是什么？不管这意味着什么，无非就是“不受约束、技术狂热的资本主义”。艾米丽认为，他的想法“极端”。这是一个相信增长、技术和资本主义必须“以几乎其他一切为代价”的人，她指的是一系列以前不为人知的“专家”在她的热门工作中提出的一系列“社会问题”。 ，但从未实际定义过。</p></blockquote><p>无论她是否对此进行了定义，我的理解是，如上所述，贝夫·杰佐斯确实认为增长、技术和资本主义必须以牺牲几乎所有其他事物为代价，包括人类灭绝的风险。这不是一种描述或稻草人，而是他愿意并且确实明确认可的声明。</p><p>那么，看起来公平吗？</p><p>相反，正如索拉纳在这里所说的那样，“e/acc 不是邪教”（例如，有效利他主义似乎越来越多地成为邪教）。在我看来，e/acc 甚至算不上一个运动。这只是一个有趣的、技术进步的模因。</p><p>是的。不，那是煤气灯操纵。无处不在的煤气灯。我受够了。</p><p>模因不会将任何在任何事情上与他们意见不同的人视为敌人，他们会不断地对他们进行人身攻击，将其描述为邪教并要求每个人都将其视为罪犯。迷因并不要求人们表明自己站在哪一边。迷因不会将忠诚徽章放入他们的简历中。模因不会写出多个宣言。正如鲁恩所观察到的，迷因并不具有迫害情结。</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p> Roon：e/accs 有一种迫害情结，很可能过度相信对他们的实际迫害。</p><p> EA 有一个卡桑德拉复合体，实际上使人们不会因为他们所做的成功预测而给予他们信任。</p></blockquote><h4 class="wp-block-heading">那么什么是E/Acc呢？</h4><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://thezvi.substack.com/i/139105207/what-about-eacc">正如我上周所说</a>，e/acc 目前在功能上是一个 Waluigi（对于 EA 的 Luigi）。我对这个模型思考得越多，它就越适合。我们看到的很多位置和我们观察到的毒性都是通过这种倒置来解释的。</p><p>我预计无论 e/acc 职位的表现如何，都会出现很多不友善的情况，因为即使是更合理的 e/acc 职位也非常不受欢迎。</p><p>他们可靠地选择的表达方式是接受某种形式的 e/acc 立场，认为这是不言而喻和正义的，而将所有其他立场视为进步和人性的敌人，并且通常不考虑他们的立场是否有意义或如何有意义的问题。它们要么对公众，要么对非常严肃的人来说。</p><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/AndrewCurran_/status/1731294547307843683">所以你会得到这样的信息，这也许是该运动的第一次高层提及：</a></p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p>安德鲁·柯兰：这就是 USSoC 雷蒙多（在里根国防论坛上）所说的：“我想说的是，硅谷有一种观点，你知道，‘快速行动，打破常规’。有效加速。我们无法通过人工智能来接受这一点。那太危险了。当你谈论人工智能时，你不能破坏东西。”</p></blockquote><p>如果你故意将这场争论定性为“e/acc vs. decel”，其理论基础是没有人会选择 decel（我的意思是你听到这听起来怎么样了吗？还要注意他们正在给大多数 95% 以上的亲技术群体贴上标签）当你离开 Twitter 和硅谷的某个特定部分时，你就会猛然惊醒。你的对手不再是支持技术的自由主义者，他们碰巧注意到了未来的某些特定问题，但大多数是你的天然盟友。相反，你进入的是政治和舆论的世界，而不是硅谷。</p><p>你知道它还有什么作用吗？它将话语变成了充满尖酸刻薄和虚假二元论的令人讨厌的污水坑。这正是自<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://thezvi.substack.com/p/openai-the-battle-of-the-board">OpenAI 董事会之战</a>以来所发生的事情，而这些类型的人确实会误解这些事件。无论如何，你站在哪一边？</p><p>这听起来像是一个稻草人， <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/robbensinger/status/1731730029686710420">但目前的中值说法比这更糟糕</a>：</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p>罗布·本辛格：“等等，你是否认为每项技术都是净积极的，我们应该始终努力走得越来越快，或者你认为进步、技术和希望是幼稚和糟糕的，我们应该禁止核电和转基因生物？”</p><p>创造新术语可以使思考变得更容易，也可以变得更困难。</p><p> “等等，你的 p(doom) 是否高于 90%，或者你认为我们应该在 AI 上走得越来越快？”一旦你考虑可能的世界国家而不仅仅是标签，这也是一个明显错误的二分法。我是作为一个 p(doom)<em>超过</em>90% 的人这么说的。</p><p> Roko（被引述）：当你花了一生的大部分时间研究一个问题，而上周听到这个问题的随机人要求你采取两个极其简单化的小丑世界立场之一，而这两个立场都基于错误的假设和逻辑错误，那么不要’不能很好地反映潜在的现实，只是最低公分母的政治部落……上帝帮助我<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3xoThNNYgZmTCpEAB/yhakkrcgoal64plohans" alt="🙏🏻" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;"></p><p> Quintessence (e/acc)（Roko 引用的内容）：等等？你是加速者还是毁灭者<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/45D7rZXiG5gCoCveM/tgwxapmuwbji4c1ulcpi" alt="🤔" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;"></p></blockquote><p>问几乎任何形式的二元问题——你是支持加速还是支持厄运（或者越来越频繁，因为厄运不被认为是足够的诽谤、减速）？ – 这是非常有力的证据，表明提问者正在采取全面的加速主义立场。否则，你会问一个更好的问题。</p><p>这是最近我们越来越多地被淹没的一个突出例子。</p><blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"><p> Eliezer Yudkowsky：切尔诺贝利爆炸的 RBMK-1000 反应堆的设计者对核反应堆物理学的理解远远超过任何人对人工智能首次创建时的理解。</p><p> <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/vkhosla/status/1731425960053064025">维诺德·科斯拉（Vinod Khosla）（VC，你知道吗？）</a> ：尽管我们看到了所有核事故，但阻止它们造成的损失远大于它所挽救的损失。像您这样的人应该咨询您的直肠科医生。你可能会找到你的头。</p><p> Eliezer Yudkowsky：如果超级智能和核反应堆一样危险，我会全力建造 100 个超级智能，并让前 99 个因为理解水平差得多而融化。第 100 个到第 1000 个 ASI 足以弥补这一点。不是我们生活的世界。</p></blockquote><p>维诺德·科斯拉 (Vinod Khosla) 在各个层面上都完全没有抓住要点，包括未能理解埃利泽 (Eliezer) 和我自己，以及几乎每个担心人工智能带来的生存风险的人，都像他一样，从根本上支持核能以及大多数其他技术进步和事物。我们可以建造。</p><p>我强调这一点是为了准确地表明，许多自称是“房间里的成年人”并玩权力游戏的人是多么不合时宜、令人无法接受的粗鲁和低级。以前情况很糟糕，但上个月变得更糟了。</p><p>再说一次，称自己为“e/acc”是为了表明你在历史上最关键问题上的立场是瓦路易吉（Waluigi），一种论证荒谬的稻草人立场。它是<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulStupid">Lawful Stupid的亲技术化身</a>。 《技术乐观主义者宣言》的立场也是如此。坚持认为那些不接受这种立场的人一定是“厄运者”或“减速者”，否则你的敌人就完全不可能进行对话。</p><p>整件事几乎就是为了引起强烈反对而设计的。</p><p>它会持续吗？ <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/alexeyguzey/status/1731380398813548975">Alexey Guzey 预测这一切都会过去，这将加速 e/acc 的消亡</a>，到 2024 年底它将消失。当然，事情进展很快。我预计一年后我们将转向不同的标签。</p><p>在一个理智的世界里，整个 e/acc 的噱头确实只是一个模因。唉，我们生活的世界并不理智。</p><p>这并不是一个独特的现象。可以说，在某种程度上，美国两大主要政党对彼此而言都是瓦路易吉斯（Waluigis）。然而，我们再次进行另一次选举。其中之一将会获胜。</p><h4 class="wp-block-heading">结论</h4><p>我将此作为参考点。这些事态的发展让我非常难过。</p><p>我不想承受这种程度的精神伤害来报告正在发生的事情。 I do not want to see people with whom I agree on most of the important things outside of AI, whose voices are badly need on a wide variety of issues strangling our civilization, to discard all nuance and civility, and then to focus entirely on one他们的立场在少数几个地方被证明是完全错误的。 <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://thezvi.substack.com/p/the-dial-of-progress">我试图提出贸易报价</a>。从本质上讲，我们得到的回报是对那些敢于倡导防止全人类死亡的人进一步发动网络人身攻击。</p><p>我仍然希望清醒的头脑能够占上风，贸易能够发生。 <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://thezvi.substack.com/i/139105207/vitalik-offers-his-version-of-techno-optimism">维塔利克的技术乐观主义版本提出了一条充满希望的潜在前进道路</a>，来自一位可信的使者，受到了广泛的欢迎。</p><p> E/acc 以仇恨另一方的名义，将多个独家立场合并到一个标签中，成功地将其声音提高到如此高的分贝水平：</p><ol><li>像贝夫·杰索斯这样的人认为人类灭绝是一个可以接受的结果。</li><li>那些认为技术总是能带来最好结果的人，因此超级智能将对人类有益。</li><li>那些实际上并不相信未来 AGI 或 ASI 的人，所以我们所做的就是构建提供普通实用程序的酷工具，让我们这样做吧。</li><li>那些认为 AGI 或 ASI 并不接近的人，让我们稍后再担心这个问题。</li><li>那些在自己的文化背景下想要站在权力一边的人。</li><li>那些不相信自己的人喜欢成为推特上的边缘领主。</li></ol><p>这六种立场的合理程度差别很大。</p><p>我相信大多数采用 e/acc 标签的人都采取了更合理的立场之一。如果这是您，我会敦促您不要采用 e/acc 标签，而是在需要时陈述您特定的合理立场及其理由，而不是将其与其他矛盾和不太合理的立场混为一谈。</p><p>或者，如果你真的像贝夫·杰索斯一样相信一套与我完全不同的价值观？那么请直接对着这个麦克风讲话。</p><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/3xoThNNYgZmTCpEAB/based-beff-jezos-and-the-accelerationists#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/3xoThNNYgZmTCpEAB/based-beff-jezos-and-the-accelerationists 3xoThNNYgZmTCPEABZvi Wed, 06 Dec 2023 16:00:09 GMT 
Bucket Brigade: Likely End-of-LifePublished on December 6, 2023 3:30 PM GMT<br/><br/><p><span>在大流行期间，我们中的一群人编写了</span><a href="https://echo.jefftk.com/">一些软件</a>，允许人们通过互联网实时唱歌和制作音乐，通过考虑延迟而不是最小化延迟。最初的目标是支持<a href="https://www.jefftk.com/p/secular-solstice-2020">2020 年世俗至日的</a>团体演唱，之后我重新设计了 UI，使其更适合<a href="https://www.jefftk.com/p/bucket-brigade-updates">演唱会</a>。现在它并没有多大用处，因为面对面一起演奏音乐更安全，但地理上分散的团体仍然会用它来唱歌。</p><p>我一直希望无限期地托管它，而我通常的方法是编写维护费用非常低的软件来<a href="https://www.jefftk.com/p/designing-low-upkeep-software">避免依赖性</a>。不幸的是，直接在浏览器 API 之上编写视频聊天软件已经足够工作，因此我依赖于 Twilio 的<a href="https://www.twilio.com/docs/video/api">可编程视频</a>产品。他们现在宣布将关闭。</p><p>他们给了一年的迁移时间，最终日期为 2024 年 12 月 5 日，但我对这个项目还不够兴奋，无法将其移植到新的视频 API。如果还有其他人，请告诉我，否则 Bucket Brigade 也会关闭。</p><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/dwPNrNF5BAdCxGcmx/bucket-brigade-likely-end-of-life#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/dwPNrNF5BAdCxGcmx/bucket-brigade-likely-end-of-life dwPNrNF5BAdCxGcmxjefftk Wed, 06 Dec 2023 15:30:07 GMT
